case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial skeletal parts only
case_circumstances: On August 7, 2012 the Jackson County Sheriff's Office recovered partial skeletal remains along a remote stretch of the Mississippi River north of Grand Tower, IL.  The bones consist of a partial mandible, the right tibia, and the right clavicle.  No other evidence was located.  An anthropologist from Southern Illinois University  believes the remains are that of a female of unknown ancestry, between 18 and 23 years old, 5'3" to 5'8" tall.  She believes the post mortem period to be between 5 and 25 years with at least part of that time spent in burial.
